# {{ project_name }} — AGENTS.md

This project uses the **morpheus-platform** (`v{{ platform_version | default("0.1.0") }}`)
via the **brownfield overlay**. This file is the generic agent entry point
(Cursor, Continue, Cline, any tool that reads `AGENTS.md`).

## Read order for every new conversation

1. [`.agent/constitution.md`](./.agent/constitution.md) — project law. Binding.
2. `platform-manifest.json` — installed profile, stacks, workspace, PM, git.
3. [`.agent/BROWNFIELD_NOTES.md`](./.agent/BROWNFIELD_NOTES.md) — what the
   overlay backed up on this repo and where originals live.
4. The relevant spec under `.agent/features/<feature_slug>/spec.md` when
   working on a specific feature.
5. [`.agent/skills/`](./.agent/skills/) — pick the right skill before acting.

## How to invoke skills

- Each skill is a markdown file with YAML frontmatter under `.agent/skills/`.
- Frontmatter declares `when_to_use`, `when_not_to_use`, `inputs`, `outputs`,
  and `requires_profiles`.
- If your profile is not in `requires_profiles`, do not invoke the skill.

